name: Inlet
headline: AI-powered ETL for complex data
description:
Inlet gets customer data into your system.

B2B companies use Inlet to sync data from ERPs and other sources, connect to any API, and transform data quickly with our AI tools.

Reach out:

founders@getinlet.ai

founders.name: Sean Adler, Founder
founders.description: Sean is co-founder and CEO of Inlet. 10+ years writing code and building AI products at startups. Previously at AKASA (Head of NLP) and ASAPP (ML Engineer).

founders.name: Adam Miller, Founder
founders.description: Co-founder and CTO of Inlet. Previously lead product and machine learning teams at Gridspace, where we built best-in-class voicebots to automate complex contact center workflows. Now building Inlet. Would love to talk, just reach out!

Features
## Why choose Inlet?
Speed up your data integrations with AI-powered tools.
### Data Mapper
AI-powered field mapping that instantly updates your code. Built-in support for Python and dbt.
![Data Mapper Illustration](https://5yomn7xwc3dminnz.public.blob.vercel-storage.com/public/Mapping%20Diagram%20\(3\)-NidLXbh5xzfk9Uhff0x6lkqGaKIBdf.png)
### AI Assistant
Our assistant helps you explore customer data, brainstorm integration design, and update mapping code.
![AI Assistant Illustration](https://5yomn7xwc3dminnz.public.blob.vercel-storage.com/public/mock-assistant-02-ktyPHwmRIUBKLeIqiym3WHJmksSjZ9.png)
### Scheduled Pipelines
Scheduled jobs run with fault tolerance and fair queueing, to ensure your syncs run flawlessly.
![Scheduled Pipelines Illustration](https://5yomn7xwc3dminnz.public.blob.vercel-storage.com/public/scheduling%20diagram%20\(8\)-68jfzQUX9yS2AHpPuNU8nQDmYSBj46.png)
### 100+ App Connectors
Built-in connectors for the most widely used apps across ERP, TMS, cybersecurity, and more.
![App Connectors Illustration](https://5yomn7xwc3dminnz.public.blob.vercel-storage.com/public/olp1-oINie3afwmfLrIb6CUdRSgxaGL6SPf.png)
### API Browser
Generate an interactive browser for any API, letting you quickly view documentation and make requests.
![API Indexing Illustration](https://5yomn7xwc3dminnz.public.blob.vercel-storage.com/public/nlp1-V3SBn8TN0RX6h5GPzpmFdimQaTWETE.png)

generated_description:
**Inlet: AI-Powered ETL for Complex Data**

Inlet is a fresh entry into the world of data management, founded in 2023 as a part of the Y Combinator Batch S23, and based in New York City. Their mission is simple yet ambitious: to provide an AI-driven ETL (Extract, Transform, Load) solution that helps businesses seamlessly integrate complex data from various sources.

**What They Do:**

Inlet specializes in connecting B2B companies with their customer data, streamlining the process of data synchronization from ERPs and other disparate sources through a user-friendly API. Their AI tools allow businesses to transform and map data with impressive speed, which translates into implementations being finished up to eight times faster and with fewer errors.

**Core Features:**

1. **Data Mapper:** This feature utilizes AI to facilitate field mapping, enabling instant updates to your code with built-in support for Python and dbt.
   
2. **AI Assistant:** An intelligent helper that guides users in exploring customer data, integrating design ideas, and updating mapping code.

3. **Scheduled Pipelines:** These ensure that data syncs occur without hitches, thanks to fault tolerance and fair queueing systems.

4. **100+ App Connectors:** Inlet comes packed with pre-built connectors for widely-used applications across sectors like ERP and TMS.

5. **API Browser:** This unique tool allows users to create an interactive interface for any API, making it easier to access documentation and execute requests.

**Why Choose Inlet?**

Users testify that Inlet dramatically slashes integration time—from weeks down to just days—while reducing maintenance work significantly. For instance, Sasha Oelsner, a Senior Data Manager at Smartwyre, claims, “Inlet cut our integration time from weeks to just 2 days. Our whole team can now build integrations with minimal training, leading us to see 80% less maintenance work.”

**The Team and Leadership:**

Currently, the core team consists of two employees, guided by Dalton Caldwell as their Group Partner. Though it’s a small team, they are clearly making waves in the industry.

**Reach Out:**

If you’re interested in learning more about Inlet or would like a demo, you can reach them at [founders@getinlet.ai](mailto:founders@getinlet.ai) or visit their website at [getinlet.ai](https://getinlet.ai).

Inlet represents a leap towards a more efficient data landscape, utilizing AI for quicker, more reliable integrations. If you're in need of robust data solutions, this is a company worth your attention.
